emails.subject: Oude Delft
emails.body:
Dear Zeno,

I am excited to say I am moving into Oude Delft 60 a, we need to do some
repairs first with the wall dampness, but I should be moving in March 1st.

I am curious about what you have done in terms of the housing insurance,
which provider have you used?

Many thanks,
Emil

emails.subject: Oude Delft 60
emails.body:
Dear Rens,

My family and I have reflected over the weekend and we would like to move
forward. I have two questions.

1. I need to transfer the deposit. What is the IBAN number of the solicitor?

2. Although we will wait with the toilet, we would like to move ahead
quickly in February to deal with the rising ground damp and the exposure of
the wall by the radiator. Do you think it would be possible to line up van
Lierop to do these two jobs in early February shortly after we take
possession? We can of course call them.

Many thanks,
Emil

emails.subject: Oude Delft
emails.body:
Dear Rens,

Thank you for your call earlier. First we would like to summarise the
situation with Oude Delft and how we would fix it. Most immediately there
is a ground water problem that needs to be fixed as a matter of urgency.
For this we have a quote to fix it of 3800 euros. There is also damp in the
wall by a radiator in the living room. The cause of this is unknown but
could be a leak from the radiator. So someone needs to open up the wall and
try to fix it. This should be done at the same time as previous problem.
Once these are completed Emil can move in.

Lastly there is a significant water build up in the wall behind the shower
and toilet. This issue is less urgent and we can wait for 6 months living
there to see how it develops and what the cause is (leaky tiles, leak from
the roof or directly from the back wall).
It is quite likely that the resolution will require significant renovations
to the bathroom and toilet. And something will need to be done to protect
the back wall and this would need to be done jointly with the upstairs
owner.

<https://www.google.com/maps/search/Verwersdijk+106+%0D%0A+Vrouwjuttenland?entry=gmail&source=g>
We need a little time to think about our options. As far as other
properties are concerned there are some other options that look interesting:

Verwersdijk 106
<https://www.funda.nl/koop/delft/huis-42349523-verwersdijk-106/>
Vrouwjuttenland 4
<https://www.funda.nl/koop/delft/appartement-42344943-vrouwjuttenland-4/>
Brabantse Turfmarkt 19 a
<https://www.funda.nl/koop/delft/appartement-42333138-brabantse-turfmarkt-19-a/>

We have written to the selling agents to enquire about their status.

Many thanks,
Emil

emails.subject: Questions for Oude Delft

I am wondering if we can have a call about what the following steps are for

of attorney, and what is still required before the transfer, assuming the
water dampness is not extensive.

Many thanks,
Emil

emails.subject: Oude Delft and Other viewings
emails.body:
Hi Rens,

My mum is coming this Friday to Delft, and we are wondering if we can see
Oude Delft one last time as she hasn't seen it.  It would have to be Friday
morning so between 9 am and 1:30 pm (preferably more towards 1:30).

We also had a few questions/things-to-confirm we wanted to ask the owner:

1. What is still going to be done by the owner?

2. What is the condition of the original flooring in the study where the
floor is elevated?

3. What is the energy label of the property, or, if not available, what was
it before the house was separated?

As well as this, we want to look at a few more places. I've put a few
places we think are promising:

https://www.funda.nl/en/koop/delft/huis-88738656-raamstraat-122/

https://www.funda.nl/en/koop/delft/huis-42397893-singelstraat-34/

https://www.funda.nl/en/koop/delft/huis-42300315-cellebroerstraat-9/

https://www.funda.nl/en/koop/delft/huis-42392572-gasthuislaan-251/

https://www.funda.nl/en/koop/delft/appartement-42302331-ezelsveldlaan-84/

Many thanks,
Emil

emails.subject: Oude Delft 60 a
emails.body:
I havent sent this yet just wrote down my thoughts.

Dear Rens / Lisette,

Before making a bid on Oude Delft 60 a, we have a few questions we wanted
to ask the owner.

1. What is still going to be done by the owner?

2. What is the condition of the original flooring in the study where the
floor is elevated?

3. What is the energy label of the property, or, if not available, what was
it before the house was separated?

Finally, Rens said he believes the value is between 365.000 and 375.000,
would 365.000 be a good starting bid?

Many thanks,
Emil

emails.subject: Oude Delft 60 a
emails.body:
Dear Rens,

We are interested in making a bid on Oude Delft 60 a, however, feel that it
is overpriced. Comparing it to Oude Delft 60 b which sold at 3.595 EUR/m^2,
this would put Oude Delft 60 a at 335.000 EUR.

We want to know what you feel a fair valuation is before we proceed with a
bid.

Many thanks,
Emil Lambert

emails.subject: Oude Delft
emails.body:
Dear Zeno,

I am excited to say I am moving into Oude Delft 60 a, we need to do some
repairs first with the wall dampness, but I should be moving in March 1st.

I am curious about what you have done in terms of the housing insurance,
which provider have you used?

Many thanks,
Emil

emails.subject: Oude Delft 60
emails.body:
Dear Rens,

My family and I have reflected over the weekend and we would like to move
forward. I have two questions.

1. I need to transfer the deposit. What is the IBAN number of the solicitor?

2. Although we will wait with the toilet, we would like to move ahead
quickly in February to deal with the rising ground damp and the exposure of
the wall by the radiator. Do you think it would be possible to line up van
Lierop to do these two jobs in early February shortly after we take
possession? We can of course call them.

Many thanks,
Emil

emails.subject: Oude Delft
emails.body:
Dear Rens,

Thank you for your call earlier. First we would like to summarise the
situation with Oude Delft and how we would fix it. Most immediately there
is a ground water problem that needs to be fixed as a matter of urgency.
For this we have a quote to fix it of 3800 euros. There is also damp in the
wall by a radiator in the living room. The cause of this is unknown but
could be a leak from the radiator. So someone needs to open up the wall and
try to fix it. This should be done at the same time as previous problem.
Once these are completed Emil can move in.

Lastly there is a significant water build up in the wall behind the shower
and toilet. This issue is less urgent and we can wait for 6 months living
there to see how it develops and what the cause is (leaky tiles, leak from
the roof or directly from the back wall).
It is quite likely that the resolution will require significant renovations
to the bathroom and toilet. And something will need to be done to protect
the back wall and this would need to be done jointly with the upstairs
owner.

<https://www.google.com/maps/search/Verwersdijk+106+%0D%0A+Vrouwjuttenland?entry=gmail&source=g>
We need a little time to think about our options. As far as other
properties are concerned there are some other options that look interesting:

Verwersdijk 106
<https://www.funda.nl/koop/delft/huis-42349523-verwersdijk-106/>
Vrouwjuttenland 4
<https://www.funda.nl/koop/delft/appartement-42344943-vrouwjuttenland-4/>
Brabantse Turfmarkt 19 a
<https://www.funda.nl/koop/delft/appartement-42333138-brabantse-turfmarkt-19-a/>

We have written to the selling agents to enquire about their status.

Many thanks,
Emil

emails.subject: Questions for Oude Delft
emails.body:

I am wondering if we can have a call about what the following steps are for
Oude Delft 60a. For example, how we set up the building insurance, if I can
sign the koopcontract before the 5th of February, or give my mother power
of attorney, and what is still required before the transfer, assuming the
water dampness is not extensive.

Many thanks,
Emil
